imperative configuration means that to describe the configuration of the resource, you execute a command from a terminalâ€™s command prompt


Creating a Pod in Kubernetes

          <PodName>     <ImageName>
              ^             ^
              |             |
kubectl run mypod --image=nginx

Creating a deployment

kubectl create deploy mydeployment --image nginx --replicas=3

Scaling the deployment

kubectl scale --replicas=10 deployment/mydeployment


Creating the namespace

kubectl create namespace rkreddy

exposing the deployment

kubectl expose deployment mydeployment --port=8080 --target-port=80 --type=LoadBalancer


kubectl create namespace test-123 --dry-run -o yaml   -> to get the O/P in YAML Format






              
              
